author: AnsemWize
commit_message:
Add shell functionality

Add Shell functionality, resolves issue #4 and includes #5.

Enable a basic shell (Uses Popen's default shell, `/bin/sh`)
`c = delegator.run("echo $0", shell=True)` 

Use a custom shell 
`c = delegator.run("echo $0", shell="/usr/bin/zsh")`

author: AnsemWize
commit_message:
Add shell property and shell functionality to pipe+nonblocking

Add shell functionality to pipe
>>> c = delegator.run("cat ./README.rst", block=False, shell=True).pipe("fgrep 'cowsay'")
>>> print(c.out)
...    # Can also be called with ([['fortune'], ['cowsay']]).
...   # or, delegator.run('fortune').pipe('cowsay')

Add shell property
>>> c = delegator.run("echo $0", block=False, shell="/usr/bin/zsh")
>>> print(c.shell)
... /usr/bin/zsh
